  "referred_to_by": [
    {
      "type": "LinguisticObject",
      "content": "This is a topographical print depicting the Nieuwe Brouwerskolk (New Brewers' Pool) at Overveen, near Haarlem, engraved by Antoine Alexandre Joseph Cardon (1739–1822) after a drawing by Augustijn Claterbos (1750–1828). It is part of a series of views of Haarlem and environs published by \"de Compagnie\" in Haarlem, c. 1790–1795. This impression is a proof print (proefdruk) on blue paper, making it a particularly rare and special impression.",
